title: WMS cross country teams compete at league meet
text: Previous Next WMS cross country teams compete at league meet The Winfield eighth grade girls cross country team receives their runner-up team medals include, from left, Clara Metzinger, Kodi Salsman, Madi Otte, Aleigha Gale and Bayleigh Harris. (Special to the Courier) Posted: Wednesday, October 14, 2015 5:33 pm WMS cross country teams compete at league meet Special to the Courier winfieldcourier.com | 0 comments Oct. 13 was a hot day in Wellington for the Pioneer League cross country meet. The Winfield Middle School girls cross country squads made it even hotter for most of the competition in their respective races, according to coach Wendy Burton. Seventh grade girls The seventh grade girls placed second out of seven teams at the Pioneer League meet with 19 points in the one-mile race.
